{"info": {"author": "voilalex", "author_email": "ilya.vouk@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.4", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.5", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.6", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.7", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries", "Topic :: Utilities"], "description": "# Cursy\n\nLittle and simple wrapper for curses application.\n\n## Getting started\n\nThe `@curses_application` decorator is a util built upon `curses.wrapper` function.\nThis decorator adds `stdscr` to `self` object on execution time of `start` method\nof the class under `@curses_application` decorator, so it can be used within the\nmethod to access the initialized curses screen.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\npip install cursy\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\n@cursy.curses_application\nclass Application:\n    def start(self):\n        self.stdscr.clear()\n        self.stdscr.addstr(0, 0, 'Hello world')\n        self.stdscr.getch()\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    app = Application()\n    app.start()\n```\n\n## License\n\n[MIT](LICENSE.md)", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "https://github.com/VoIlAlex/archive/v1.0.1.tar.gz", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/VoIlAlex/cursy", "keywords": "wrapper,console,curses,utility", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "cursy", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/cursy/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/cursy/", "project_urls": {"Download": "https://github.com/VoIlAlex/archive/v1.0.1.tar.gz", "Homepage": "https://github.com/VoIlAlex/cursy"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/cursy/1.0.1/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "Little and simple wrapper for curses application.", "version": "1.0.1", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>Cursy</h1>\n<p>Little and simple wrapper for curses application.</p>\n<h2>Getting started</h2>\n<p>The <code>@curses_application</code> decorator is a util built upon <code>curses.wrapper</code> function.\nThis decorator adds <code>stdscr</code> to <code>self</code> object on execution time of <code>start</code> method\nof the class under <code>@curses_application</code> decorator, so it can be used within the\nmethod to access the initialized curses screen.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<pre>pip install cursy\n</pre>\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<pre><span class=\"nd\">@cursy</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">curses_application</span>\n<span class=\"k\">class</span> <span class=\"nc\">Application</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"k\">def</span> <span class=\"nf\">start</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">):</span>\n        <span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">stdscr</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">clear</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n        <span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">stdscr</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">addstr</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'Hello world'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n        <span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">stdscr</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">getch</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">if</span> <span class=\"vm\">__name__</span> <span class=\"o\">==</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"__main__\"</span><span class=\"p\">:</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">app</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">Application</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n    <span class=\"n\">app</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">start</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n</pre>\n<h2>License</h2>\n<p><a href=\"LICENSE.md\" rel=\"nofollow\">MIT</a></p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 7019000, "releases": {"1.0.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "5002582f3d66f631c3cef3aa081d1ea5", "sha256": "ea3b000c8085780d73803a906c6263dca17ed452d5228bb407ee39964a08231d"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "cursy-1.0.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "5002582f3d66f631c3cef3aa081d1ea5", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 2202, "upload_time": "2020-04-03T22:51:49", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-03T22:51:49.036740Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/28/e9/f922bd579f1f0def4f5c7af55c0cd45cd84b8bcb7ca2032293761f7a2bee/cursy-1.0.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "1.0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "9eb3c0b7974741c1f5389f17976e282e", "sha256": "0c4a30121c496dc255f936eeae3dd27deee66da3b9a5e3f0adf66ab900c2bb90"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "cursy-1.0.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "9eb3c0b7974741c1f5389f17976e282e", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 2205, "upload_time": "2020-04-14T17:58:58", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-14T17:58:58.792942Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/99/51/050f9cccc26005f5b1759e13b179b321fd8d895fa6787d35242304290c71/cursy-1.0.1.tar.gz", "yanked": false}]}, "urls": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "9eb3c0b7974741c1f5389f17976e282e", "sha256": "0c4a30121c496dc255f936eeae3dd27deee66da3b9a5e3f0adf66ab900c2bb90"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "cursy-1.0.1.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "9eb3c0b7974741c1f5389f17976e282e", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 2205, "upload_time": "2020-04-14T17:58:58", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-04-1